<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written Evidence from Michael Ford</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written Evidence from Michael Ford</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Point 2: </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What are the factors which can influence police </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">mis</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">-recording of crime ?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Answer: I reported a crime (perjury) which I believed had been committed during evidence given in a High Court case by two named individuals. The High Court judges also stated in court that they required an investigation into the honesty of the same individuals. I reported the Judge’s concerns to the Police.  The Court of Appeal judges who raised questions </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in the judgment about witness </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">“dishonesty” were Lord Justice Hughes, Lord Justice </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Toulson</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and Lord Justice Sullivan in Case No. A2/2009/0206, dated 19 May 2009. It was their comments that justified my later crime complaint to the City of London Police. The Judges’ names and the 2009 High Court case details are matters of public record. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The City of London Police </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">recorded</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the crime that I suspected had been committed and it was entered in Police Records as </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">“ criminality by the senior partners of a named legal firm.”</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">But within months, junior Law Society officials, persuaded the same Police to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">de-record</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the “criminality” offence entered in the Police Record and no criminal investigation took place.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Point 5:</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Policy-makers cannot have confidence in the statistics of crime-reporting </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">f civilian persons can shield </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">individuals from prosecution by demanding that Police halt a criminal investigation. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>